now needs two more victories, tomorrow and on Monday, in order to secure a place on the plane to Paris.\", \"from\": 291, \"to\": 398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 392, \"end\": 397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998706769103, \"rank\": 1.293230767842411e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Facing German opponent Stefanie Von Berge, Walsh lost the opening round on four of the five judge's scorecards this morning, leaving her with an uphill battle to keep her Olympic dream alive.\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 407, \"end\": 413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.977121831377683, \"rank\": 0.021549208068692354, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A brilliant second round from the Offaly woman, in which she took the fight to Von Berge and rattled off some excellent combination punches, put her back in contention on the judges' cards.\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 627, \"end\": 633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Offaly_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9999999999993179, \"rank\": 5.48144927952281e-13, \"text\": \"Offaly\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Offaly_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Offaly_GAA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It then came down to a hard-fought final round in which Walsh would not be denied, showing tremendous resolve once again to land some big punches.\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 930, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the decision was being announced, both boxers had their fists up, ready to celebrate, but the verdict was in Walsh's favour on a 3-2 split.\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 1074, \"entities\": []}, {\"s